# Chart Registry Contract

All chart types live in `echartsRegistry.js` under `ECHARTS_TYPES`. Every entry must implement the full interface — partial entries will break the fallback logic in `actionExecutor.js`.

## Required Interface

```js
// ✅ Every chart type must have ALL five properties
ECHARTS_TYPES = {
  MY_CHART: {
    id: 'my_chart',                    // lowercase, matches the object key
    label: 'My Chart',                 // human-readable display name
    icon: SomeLucideIcon,              // Lucide icon component
    isSupported: (dims, measures) =>   // NEVER omit — fallback logic depends on it
      dims === 1 && measures === 1,
    createOption: (data, payload) => { // returns a plain ECharts option object only
      // ...
    },
  },
}
```

## Enhancement Pipeline — Strict Layer Separation

Chart creation follows a three-stage pipeline. **Do not skip stages or cross layer boundaries.**

```
createOption(data, payload)          ← data mapping only
       ↓
applyUniversalEnhancements(option)   ← visual polish applied here
       ↓
<EChartsWrapper option={option} />   ← rendering
```

### What belongs in `createOption`
- Mapping `data` rows to ECharts `series`, `xAxis`, `yAxis`
- Setting chart-type-specific layout properties
- Reading `payload.statistics` to pass values downstream

### What does NOT belong in `createOption`
```js
// ❌ Do not call enhancement helpers inside createOption
createOption: (data, payload) => {
  const zoom = createSliderDataZoom(data.length);  // ❌ wrong layer
  const tooltip = createBarChartTooltip(...);      // ❌ wrong layer
}

// ✅ These are applied by enhancementApplier.js automatically
// Just return the base option from createOption
```

### Where visual enhancements live

| Concern | File |
|---------|------|
| Mark lines, quartile bands, zoom sliders | `visualEnhancements.js` |
| Tooltip formatters | `tooltipFactory.js` |
| Axis label truncation / smart labels | `labelHelper.js` |
| Applying all of the above | `enhancementApplier.js` |

## Compatibility Matrix

When adding a new chart type, set `isSupported` to match exactly one row:

| dims | measures | Suitable chart types |
|------|----------|----------------------|
| 1 | 1 | bar, pie, line, funnel, treemap |
| 1 | 2 | scatter, grouped_bar, dual_axis |
| 2 | 1 | stacked_bar, bubble, treemap |
| 1 | 3–5 | multi_series_bar, line |
| 0 | 1 | gauge |
| 1 | 4 | candlestick |

## Shared Utilities

```js
// ✅ Use the shared truncateText from src/lib/utils.js
import { truncateText } from '../../lib/utils';

// ❌ Do not redefine truncateText locally in registry files
function truncateText(text, maxLength) { ... }
```
